{{short description|20th and 21st-century Bolivian Catholic bishop}} {{spanish name|Costas|Montaño}} {{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | honorific-prefix = His Excellency | name = Abel Costas Montaño | title = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Tarija|Bishop Emeritus of Tarija]] | image = | alt = | caption = | church = [[Roman Catholic Church]] | see = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Tarija|Diocese of Tarija]] | term = 1974–1995 | term_end = 20 October 1995 | predecessor = Juan Niccolai | successor = Adhemar Esquivel Kohenque <!-- Orders --> | ordination = 22 September 1945 | ordinated_by = | consecration = 6 January 1969 | consecrated_by = [[Paul VI]] | rank = <!-- Personal details --> | birth_date = {{birth date|1920|5|25}} | birth_place = [[Pocona| Pocona, Bolivia]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2015|2|11|1920|5|25}} | death_place = [[Cercado Province (Cochabamba)|Cercado]], [[Bolivia]] | previous_post = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Cochabamba|Auxiliary Bishop of Cochabamba]] <small>(1968-1974)</small> | nationality = [[Bolivian people|Bolivian]] }}
'''Abel Costas Montaño''' (May 25, 1920&nbsp;– February 11, 2015) was a [[Bolivia]]n [[prelate]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church]].
Costas Montaño was born in Pocona, Bolivia and was ordained a priest on September 22, 1945. He was appointed auxiliary archbishop of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Cochabamba|Archdiocese of Cochabamba]] on November 11, 1968, as well as titular bishop of Novi, and was ordained bishop on January 6, 1969. Montaño was appointed Bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Tarija|Diocese of Tarija]] on December 11, 1974, where he would serve until his retirement on October 20, 1995.
