'''Hinduism''' is the fastest growing religion '''in Northern Ireland''' with over 2400 [[Hinduism|Hindus]] (up from 825 in 2001, a 188% increase) in the country, making up 0.13%(up from 0.05% in the 2001 census).<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/northernireland/schools/4_11/pfocus/citizenship/spring2001/ Programme 1 - Indian Community] bbc.c.uk, accessed 10 January 2009</ref> There are currently 3 [[Mandirs]] in [[Belfast]] alone: Radha-Krishna Temple in [[Malone Road]], Laxmi-Narayan Mandir in Clifton Street and Radha Madhava Mandir ([[ISKCON]]) in Upper Dunmurry Lane.<ref>[http://www.nhsf.org.uk/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=46&Itemid=119 Mandirs in Northern Ireland ] National Hindu Students Forum, accessed 10 January 2009</ref> There is also a Hare Krishna Centre on [[Inis Rath|Inish Rath]] Island that was established in 1985.<ref>[http://www.culturenorthernireland.org/article.aspx?art_id=77 The Hare Krishna Centre] culturenorthernireland.org, accessed 10 January 2009</ref>
