{{Orphan|date=March 2018}} {{Jews and Judaism sidebar|religion}}
'''Choral synagogues''' ({{lang-yi|Khorshul}}) were built in Eastern Europe, from Hungary to Russia.<ref name=yivo/> These synagogues represented the ideas of Jewish Enlightenment (''[[Haskalah]]'') and made certain reforms to the traditional Jewish customs (''[[minhag]]'').<ref name=meir/> Often, they featured male choruses, conducted sermons in local languages (German, Russian, etc.), enforced order during services, decorated their interior, and placed [[pew]]s facing eastern wall where the [[Torah ark]] was displayed (in traditionalist synagogues, the ark and [[Bema|bimah]] stood in the center of the room).<ref name=yivo/><ref name=meir/> However, the changes did not extend to religious beliefs and customs. Therefore, the differences between choral and traditional synagogues are more aesthetic.<ref name=levin/>
==Active choral synagogues== * [[Moscow Choral Synagogue]] of [[Moscow]] * [[Grand Choral Synagogue]] of [[St. Petersburg]] * [[Great Choral Synagogue]] of [[Kiev]] * [[Brodsky Synagogue]] of [[Kiev]] * [[Kharkiv Choral Synagogue]] * [[Great Synagogue (Hrodna)|Great Synagogue of Hrodna]] * [[Choral Synagogue, Vilnius|Vilnius Choral Synagogue]] of [[Vilnius]] * [[Kaunas Synagogue|Kaunas Choral Synagogue]] of [[Kaunas]] * [[Templul Coral]] in [[Bucharest]] * Great Choral Synagogue of [[Odessa]] * [[Golden Rose Synagogue (Dnipropetrovsk)]]
==Defunct choral synagogues== * [[Great Choral Synagogue, Riga|Great Choral Synagogue of Riga]] ([[Burning of the Riga synagogues|burned in 1941]]) * Great Choral Synagogue of [[Daugavpils]] * Great Choral Synagogue of [[Šiauliai]] * Choral Synagogue in [[Samara, Russia|Samara]] (closed in 1929, being restored) * [[Choral Synagogue (Smolensk)|Choral Synagogue in Smolensk]] (occupied by a school) * Choral Synagogue of [[Drohobych]] * Choral Synagogue in [[Białystok]] (burned during the liquidation of the [[Białystok Ghetto]]) * Choral Synagogue in [[Vitebsk]] * Choral Synagogue in [[Minsk]] (occupied by a theater) * Choral Synagogue in [[Brest, Belarus|Brest]] * Choral Synagogue of [[Liepāja]] * Choral Synagogue in [[Chișinău]] * Choral Synagogue in [[Tallinn]] (destroyed during [[Bombing of Tallinn in World War II|bombing in 1944]])
