'''Lubavitch Youth Organization''' ('''LYO''') is an organization run by [[Chabad]], a [[Jewish]], [[Hasidic]] movement. The organization offers a range of services for Jews of all affiliations. LYO was established by Chabad [[rebbe]], [[Rabbi]] [[Menachem Mendel Schneerson]] in 1955.<ref>Lubavitchyouth.org. "Homepage". ''Lubavitch Youth Organization''. [http://www.lubavitchyouth.org LYO homepage]</ref><ref name="JTA">[http://www.jta.org/1974/03/26/archive/lubavitch-youth-organization-praised Lubavitch Youth Organization Praised. ''JTA.org''. March 26, 1974.]</ref>
==Administration== *'''Chairman:''' Rabbi [[Dovid Raskin]] (d. 2011).<ref name="ChabadObit">[http://www.chabad.org/news/article_cdo/aid/1522716/jewish/Longtime-Lubavitch-Youth-Leader-Passes-Away.htm Zaklikowski, Dovid. "Longtime Lubavitch Youth Leader Passes Away" ''Chabad.org''. May 17, 2011.]</ref><ref name="ColliveObit">[http://www.collive.com/show_news.rtx?id=14421 Collive Reporter. "Rabbi Dovid Raskin, 84, OBM". ''Collive.com'' May 10, 2011.]</ref><ref>[http://crownheights.info/notices/34508/boruch-dayan-hoemes-rabbi-dovid-raskin-obm/ "Boruch Dayan Hoemes – Rabbi Dovid Raskin OBM". ''CrownHeights.info''. May 10, 2011.]</ref><ref>[http://lubavitch.com/news/article/2030983/Senior-Member-of-Chabad-Leadership-84.html Chabad Lubavitch Headquarters. "Senior Member of Chabad Leadership, 84". ''Lubavitch.com''. May 11, 2011.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130501230402/http://lubavitch.com/news/article/2030983/Senior-Member-of-Chabad-Leadership-84.html |date=May 1, 2013 }}</ref> *'''Director:''' Rabbi [[Shmuel Butman|Shmuel M. Butman]].<ref>Chabad.org. "Lubavitch Youth Organization Headquarters". ''Chabad.org''. [http://www.chabad.org/centers/default_cdo/aid/117669/jewish/Lubavitch-Youth-Organization.htm Chabad.org directory]</ref>
