{{italictitle}} '''''Sodom and Gomorrah: The Last Seven Days''''' is a 1975 pornographic film directed and produced by the [[Mitchell brothers]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tcm.com/tcmdb/title/486828/Sodom-and-Gomorrah/|title=Sodom and Gomorrah (1975) - Overview - TCM.com|website=Turner Classic Movies}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.be/books?id=8Dzkz41fHlsC&pg=PA64&lpg=PA64&dq=Sodom+and+gomorrah:+the+last+seven+days&source=bl&ots=bu93-2rB_m&sig=cESniwOYGAE3F6dJjnNqKZ3aF7E&hl=nl&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiP95qe2dbZAhVLIMAKHbroBhI4FBDoAQhHMAU#v=onepage&q=Sodom+and+gomorrah:+the+last+seven+days&f=false|title=Gutter Auteur: The Films of Andy Milligan|first=Rob|last=Craig|date=27 November 2012|publisher=McFarland|via=Google Books}}</ref> set in [[Bible|biblical times]].<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=http://www.houstonpress.com/arts/5-surreal-moments-in-pornographic-film-history-6395301|title=5 Surreal Moments in Pornographic Film History|first=Chris|last=Lane|date=5 August 2014|publisher=}}</ref> It's a free interpretation of the tale of [[Sodom and Gomorrah]], with a subplot where extraterrestrial aliens observe Earth.<ref name="auto"/> The space captain of their ship has the physical appearance of a [[chimpanzee]] and speaks with a voice which imitates [[John Wayne]].<ref name="sextech.com">{{cite web|url=https://sextech.com/sex/retro-porn/retro-porn-review-sodom-and-gomorrah-the-last-seven-days/|title=Retro Porn Review - Sodom and Gomorrah: The Last Seven Days|date=5 July 2015|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chicagoreader.com/Bleader/archives/2011/12/21/testament-week-the-book-of-jim-and-artie|title=Testament Week: the Book of Jim & Artie|first=Ben|last=Sachs|publisher=}}</ref> The picture had a budget of 1 million dollars,<ref name="auto1">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.be/books?id=JBctCwAAQBAJ&pg=PA270&lpg=PA270&dq=Sodom+and+gomorrah:+the+last+seven+days&source=bl&ots=Wdy-07Qg0l&sig=PiD57w1_nQGGpjWC5Nqvm-V8YWQ&hl=nl&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi7wMOr2dbZAhWLJsAKHZdCDS84HhDoAQg2MAI#v=onepage&q=Sodom+and+gomorrah:+the+last+seven+days&f=false|title=Dirty Words and Filthy Pictures: Film and the First Amendment|first=Jeremy|last=Geltzer|date=4 January 2016|publisher=University of Texas Press|via=Google Books}}</ref> and the soundtrack was created by [[Mike Bloomfield]] and [[Barry Goldberg]].<ref name="sextech.com"/> Nevertheless, it was a huge flop at the box office.<ref name="auto1"/>
==Plot==
Lot and his family move to [[Sodom and Gomorrah|Sodom]], where king Bera rules. He hopes to start a life as a merchant, but is instead confronted with the strange laws of the city, which forbid vaginal intercourse. Meanwhile, the events are witnessed by an extraterrestrial spaceship which has a monkey for a captain.
